<class module="videoDriver" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.videoDriver.display.BIVideoDisplayDeviceExt" name="BIVideoDisplayDeviceExt" packageName="com.tridium.videoDriver.display" public="true" interface="true" abstract="true" category="interface">
<description>
This is analogous to the point device extension in ordinary Niagara AX&#xa; drivers. However, instead of acting as the root container for data points,&#xa; this acts as the root container for video displays (BIVideoDisplay components).&#xa; &#xa; BIVideoSystem components have a BIVideoDisplayDeviceExt. A BIVideoDvr is one&#xa; such example of a BIVideoSystem.
</description>
